\begin_layout Chapter
Overview
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align block
Volunteers for Salesforce is a Salesforce package that can be installed
 into any Salesforce instance, and used to manage all aspects of your organizati
on’s volunteer management needs.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align block
Volunteers are managed in Salesforce using Contacts, Campaigns, and several
 custom objects, summarized below:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\align block
Volunteer Job – used to specify a job or position that needs to be filled,
 as well as the skills needed for the job.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\align block
Volunteer Shift – used to specify dates, times, and number of volunteers
 needed for a specific Volunteer Job.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\align block
Volunteer Hours – used to track the hours a volunteer spends for your organizati
on, including the date(s) worked, the hours spent, and the volunteer job
 it was for.
 Can also specify the specific job shift the volunteer filled.
 Also used to tentatively schedule volunteers for specific job shifts and
 positions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align block
Volunteer information about Contacts is stored in several custom fields
 which include Availability, Skills, Status, and a summary of the Hours
 worked.
 Leads also have some additional custom fields for tracking volunteer informatio
n.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align block
Campaigns have several custom fields added to them to show a summary information
 of the number of hours and number of volunteers who have worked on all
 Volunteer Jobs in the Campaign.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chapter
Installation Instructions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Groundwire Volunteers for Salesforce package is available as a managed
 package and source code.
 Visit the AppExchange for the managed project 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "here"
target "http://appexchange.salesforce.com/listingDetail?listingId=a0N30000003JBggEAG"

\end_inset

, or the Google Code project 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "here"
target "http://code.google.com/p/groundwire-volunteers-for-salesforce/"

\end_inset

 to find the links to the source code (for advanced users).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Requirements Before Installing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
marginnote{
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\series bold
If you have 6 or more rollup summary fields on the Campaign object, Volunteers
 for Salesforce will fail to install and you must have Salesforce increase
 your rollup summary field limit before installing.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\series default
In order to successfully install the package and to have the tests run without
 any errors, you must ensure that the login used to install the package
 has permissions to create Campaigns (they must have Marketing User checked
 in their user account), as well as permissions to install packages.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Creating a default Campaign record type (optional)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
marginnote{
\end_layout

\end_inset

Note: This step is optional.
 It is included so that you may preserve the way Salesforce handles Campaigns
 by default (which may or may not be useful to your organization).
 It is safe to skip this step, as it can be done later if you decide you
 wish to choose between the default Salesforce Campaign and the Volunteers
 campaign.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since the Volunteers package will create a new Campaign Record Type, you
 should first create a default Campaign Record Type, if you don’t have one.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Click on your username in the top right and go down to Setup.
 
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Images/usermenu.png
	scale 60

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pagebreak
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
In the navigation on the left go to App Setup > Customize > Campaigns >
 Record Types.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Images/campaign-app-setup.png
	scale 50

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Click on the “New” button.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Images/campaign-record-type-new.png
	scale 40

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Use “—Master—“ in the Existing Record Type picklist.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Images/campaign-record-new-create.png
	scale 60

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Fill in Record Type Label.
 We suggest “Default” 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Use the Record Type Name that Salesforce fills in, when you fill out the
 Record Type Label.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
For description, put in “The default campaign record type to use for new
 campaigns.” 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Check “Active”.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Check the “Enable For Profile” checkbox in the header, so that all profiles
 can use this new record type.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Images/campaign-record-profile-settings.png
	scale 60

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Check the “Make Default” checkbox in the header, so that all profiles will
 default to using this new record type.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Click “Next”.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
On the Assign Page Layouts page, choose Apply one layout to all profiles,
 and select “Campaign layout”, or whatever your default page layout should
 be.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash

\backslash

\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Graphics
	filename Images/campaign-record-default-layout.png
	scale 50

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Click “Save”.
\end_layout

